article.description: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 75, Fairleigh Dickinson 68
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 75, Fairleigh Dickinson 68
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 75, Fairleigh Dickinson 68
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- Kelly Beidler scored 22 points and pulled down seven rebounds to lead Mount St. Mary's of Maryland to a 75-68 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday night. Jeremy Goode added 18 points and handed out five assists for the Mount (14-10, 9-4 in Northeast Conference), while Jean Cajou finished with 14 points. Sean Baptiste had 27 points for the Knights (6-18, 5-8), while Terence Grier and Kamil Svrdlik scored 11 points each and Cameron Tyler finished with 10 points and 11 assists. Mount St. Mary's opened the game with an 11-0 run and led 32-25 at the break. FDU tried to rally early on in the second half, but the Mount responded with a 15-5 run and then held double-digit leads for most of the half. The Mount also won the battle of the boards, outrebounding the Knights 36-28.
